about.summary: sphinxcontrib-serializinghtml is a sphinx extension which outputs "serialized" HTML files (json and pickle).

name: sphinxcontrib-serializinghtml
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.1.3" %}

package:
  name: sphinxcontrib-serializinghtml
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/s/sphinxcontrib-serializinghtml/sphinxcontrib-serializinghtml-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c0efb33f8052c04fd7a26c0a07f1678e8512e0faec19f4aa8f2473a8b81d5227

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.5
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.5

test:
  requires:
    # This is a circular dependency b/c sphinx depends on this package now :-/
    - sphinx
  imports:
    - sphinxcontrib
    - sphinxcontrib.serializinghtml

about:
  home: http://sphinx-doc.org/
  license: BSD-2-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: sphinxcontrib-serializinghtml is a sphinx extension which outputs "serialized" HTML files (json and pickle).

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ocefpaf
